<paragraph id="390236EBD050FFEDC18AF92DFD876147" blockId="2.[136,1452,1787,1886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="211">
Endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="FB79F809D050FFEDC012F92DFEA7610C" box="[272,379,1787,1813]" country="Australia" name="Tasmania" pageId="2" pageNumber="211">Tasmania</collectingRegion>
where it is an occasional epiphyte on shaded, smooth bark in rainforest. This species is clearly closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="FEBD4D68D050FFEDC04FF8F6FE256120" box="[333,505,1823,1849]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Xylographaceae" genus="Lambiella" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="2" pageNumber="211" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="globulispora">
<emphasis id="0BC9EAF9D050FFEDC04FF8F6FE256120" box="[333,505,1823,1849]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="211">L. globulispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FEBD4D68D050FFEDC304F8F6FD4A6120" box="[518,662,1823,1849]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Xylographaceae" genus="Lambiella" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="2" pageNumber="211" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="umbratilis">
<emphasis id="0BC9EAF9D050FFEDC304F8F6FD4A6120" box="[518,662,1823,1849]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="211">L. umbratilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
